1. Admin / User Upload System (Day 10)
Status: Missing


Requirement: The documentation requires an "Admin upload system" to "Upload audio files" manually and "Store metadata in DB".
+2

Current State: Your app.py has an UPLOAD_FOLDER, but it is currently used only for downloading tracks from YouTube (yt_dlp). You lack an API endpoint allowing a user to upload their own MP3 file from their computer.

Task:

Create a frontend UI in Sidebar.jsx (you already have an "Upload" tab placeholder) to select a file.

Create a Flask endpoint (e.g., /api/upload) to accept multipart/form-data, save the file, and create a Track entry in the database.

2. Resume Playback Logic (Day 9)
Status: Partially Complete


Requirement: "Resume playback from last position".


Current State: Your app.py (history_update) and models.py (RecentlyPlayed) successfully save the timestamp. However, your PlayerContext.jsx does not seem to use this timestamp to seek to the correct second when a song starts.

Task:

Update playSong in PlayerContext.jsx to check if a timestamp exists for that song and set audioRef.current.currentTime accordingly upon load.

3. Security & Optimization (Day 12)
Status: Missing


Requirement: "Rate limiting" and "Code refactoring".

Current State:

Refactoring: Your app.py is becoming large. Standard practice is to move routes into "Blueprints" (e.g., routes/auth.py, routes/player.py).

Rate Limiting: You need to install Flask-Limiter to prevent API abuse.

Secrets: Your JWT_SECRET_KEY is currently hardcoded ('dev-secret-key'). This needs to move to an .env file for "Production-ready backend" status.

